value.name: Kainé | NIER Wiki | Fandom
value.snippet: Kainé is a companion and deuteragonist of NieR, who accompanies Nier after he helps her kill Hook. The left side of her body is possessed by a Shade who dubs himself Tyrann. As a result of her upbringing and Tyrann's occupation of her body, she has a disposition towards being crude and violent...

value.name: Nier Replicant: 14 Things You Didn't Know About Kaine - TheGamer
value.snippet: Kaine is an intersex woman who isn't afraid to speak her mind, dress how she feels, and use colorful language to express herself. Kaine is also a kind character who is shown comforting young Emil, who had also become an outcast among humanity.

value.name: Where does the name Kainé come from? : r/nier
value.snippet: The title is pretty self-explanatory. This character has to be one of my favourite, and still I have no clue about the origin or the meaning of her name. Given that Yoko Taro seems to take no thing for granted, I was hoping to discover something more about Kainé by this. Thanks you in advance.

value.name: Kainé | Nier Replicant Wiki
value.snippet: Kainé is an NPC in Nier Replicant and one of NieR's companions. She is one of three of his companions-- the white book, Grimoire Weiss, and Emil, who follow him in the game.
